    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-02-08T15:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-02-08T15:43:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <head>451. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d451fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 797.00/2–856. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SHH1"
                            >Smith</persName> and initialed by <persName corresp="#p_SWJ1"
                            >Sebald</persName>. Also sent to Singapore and Kuala Lumpur and pouched
                        to Penang.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-02-08T15:43:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1956—3:43 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4439. Question communist subversion Singapore/Federation raised with Foreign
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Lloyd</persName> by Secretary last
                        week.<note n="2" xml:id="d451fn2">Reference is to the <persName
                            corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_LS1"
                            >Lloyd</persName> visit to Washington, January 31–February 1.</note>
                    Consensus was both areas very important from military political points view in
                        <gloss target="#t_SEA1">SEA</gloss> and Singapore situation of great
                    concern.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Lloyd</persName> briefly described different
                    political situations two areas, noting developments more favorable in
                    Federation. Said <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> policy is encourage Malayans
                    take on more responsibility so long as defense reserved to <gloss
                        target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, noted London talks going well.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d451fn3">Regarding these talks relating to Malayan independence, see
                            <ref target="#d452">
                            <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Lloyd</persName> commented difficult problem loyalty
                    Singapore Chinese, added if worse became worst <persName corresp="#p_MD1"
                        >Marshall</persName> apparently plans propose direct <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                        >UK</gloss> rule.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> believes leaders both areas tend look New
                    Delhi for guidance future international alignment. <persName corresp="#p_LS1"
                        >Lloyd</persName> remarked real problem will result if <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> throws weight to encompass Malaya in
                    neutralist bloc.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. Department plans further exploratory talks
                    British Embassy near future. You should await further instructions before
                    proceeding <gloss target="#t_CA1">CA</gloss>–5294.<note n="4" xml:id="d451fn4">
                        <ref target="#d449">Document 449</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
